<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-04T02:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-04T02:34:00-05:00" n="638" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1056: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJF1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-04T16:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">September 4,
                                        1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 12:30
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your cable August 21st, 5 p.m.<note n="33" xml:id="d638fn33">Not printed;
                                see telegram to the Consul at Vlaidvostok, Aug. 21, 4 p.m., <ref target="#pg_572">p. 572</ref>.</note> Allied inspectors have not
                            been withdrawn from <persName>Semenoff</persName> territory.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>